it.emarolab.owloop.descriptor.construction.descriptorExpression

Interface IndividualExpression.DataLink<D extends DataPropertyExpression>

  • Type Parameters:

    public static interface IndividualExpression.DataLink<D extends DataPropertyExpression>
extends Individual.DataLink<it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.OWLReferences,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,DescriptorEntitySet.DataLinks,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLDataProperty,D>, IndividualExpression
    The Individual.DataLink expression for a Descriptor whose ground is OWLNamedIndividual.

    It specifies how to queryDataIndividual() and writeExpressionAxioms() for the data properties associated to the ground Individual Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance(). It also implements common function to populate the ExpressionEntitySet (of type DescriptorEntitySet.DataLinks) that specify the data properties of this individualDescriptor that are synchronised with this Descriptor. For efficiency, this descriptor does not map all the properties of an individualDescriptor but only for the Expressions that have been initialised in the ExpressionEntity. On the other hand, if the set of ExpressionEntitySet is left empty during Individual.DataLink.readExpressionAxioms(), it maps all the object properties applied to the described individualDescriptor

      • removeData

        default boolean removeData(java.lang.String property,
                           java.lang.Object value)
        Remove the ExpressionEntity#getExpression() of the given property, with a specific value, from this Descriptor. This call does not remove the semantic from this object, and it may be repopulate (or completely removed) by calling: Individual.DataLink.readExpressionAxioms(). The class of the specified value represents its data type, supported OWLLiteral are: Integer, Boolean, Double, Float and Long (see DescriptorGroundInterface.getOWLLiteral(Object)).
        Parameters:
        property - the name of the data property which value, contained in getDataExpressionAxioms(), will be removed.
        value - the property value to be removed from the DescriptorEntitySet.DataLinks#getValues() set.
        Returns:
        true if an element was removed as a result of this call.

      • writeExpressionAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> writeExpressionAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update the ontology with a specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the OWL representation with the internal state of the descriptor, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet).
        Specified by:
        writeExpressionAxioms in interface Axiom.Descriptor<it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.OWLReferences,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the OWL ontology during the writing. Note that the elements of the returned list, may have the Axiom.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: OWLOntologyChange).
